e organisations are there every step of the way.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-108_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-109_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-110_">Take action</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/mental-health-2023-11-27-05-25-00-utc.jpg?v=1708434831" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/mental-health-2023-11-27-05-25-00-utc.jpg?v=1708434831 1536w" width="2000" height="1500" alt="Shedding light on postpartum depression: what you need to know - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Shedding light on postpartum depression: what you need to know - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-112_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-113_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by wanaktek via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-115_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">As we look ahead to Maternal Mental Health Awareness Week 2024, let's pledge to be advocates for change. Let's break down the barriers of stigma and shame surrounding maternal mental health. Let's amplify the voices of mothers who may feel unheard and unseen. And most importantly, let's stand together in solidarity, showing our unwavering support for the mental well-being of mothers everywhere.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-117_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-118_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-119_">Conclusion</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/mental-health-matters-motivational-quote-on-the-le-2023-11-27-05-18-40-utc.jpg?v=1708434923" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/mental-health-matters-motivational-quote-on-the-le-2023-11-27-05-18-40-utc.jpg?v=1708434923 1536w" width="2000" height="1333" alt="Empowering mothers: accessing maternal mental health support - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Empowering mothers: accessing maternal mental health support - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-121_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-122_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by OksaLy via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-124_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In the end, Maternal Mental Health Awareness Week is more than just a week on the calendar â€“ it's a movement. It's a movement towards greater understanding, empathy, and support for mothers facing mental health challenges. So, let's join hands, raise our voices, and shine a light on maternal mental health. Together, we can make a difference.<br><br>Remember, if you or someone you know is struggling, help is just a click or a call away. Reach out to organisations like PSI, RCPsych, or the MMHA for support and guidance. You are not alone, and there is always hope.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-4baa" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-uojGG hMqLeX pf-126_ pf-sm-hide pf-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-ilfuhL bpQaoh"><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-127_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-128_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/img20221214153316-1671712230191.jpg?v=1671712234" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/img20221214153316-1671712230191.jpg?v=1671712234 1536w, http